
Perfect, Rushikesh â€” youâ€™ve shared a complete Maven web project with Servlets, JSPs, Hibernate, and MySQL. Let me walk you through the sequence and flow step by step so you can visualize how everything connects. Iâ€™ll explain it like a pipeline from user â†’ servlet â†’ DAO â†’ DB â†’ JSP.

ðŸ”„ Project Flow (Step by Step)
1. User Entry Point
- The user opens register.html (your welcome file in web.xml).
- This HTML form collects name, email, mobile.
- On submit, the form sends a POST request to /register (mapped to RegisterServlet).

2. RegisterServlet.java
- Servlet receives the request (doPost).
- Extracts form data using req.getParameter("name"), etc.
- Creates a Student object and sets values.
- Calls StudentDAO.writeStudent(s) to persist the student in DB.
- After saving, redirects to success.jsp.
ðŸ‘‰ This servlet is the controller for registration.

3. Student.java (Entity Class)
- Annotated with @Entity and @Table(name="students").
- Represents the students table in MySQL.
- Fields: id, name, email, mobile.
- Hibernate uses this class to map Java objects â†” database rows.
ðŸ‘‰ This is the model in MVC.

4. StudentDAO.java (Data Access Layer)
- Handles DB operations using Hibernate.
- writeStudent(Student s):
- Loads Hibernate config (hibernate.cfg.xml).
- Opens a session, begins transaction.
- Calls session.persist(s) â†’ inserts into DB.
- Commits transaction.
- getAllStudents():
- Opens session.
- Runs HQL query from Student.
- Returns a List<Student>.
ðŸ‘‰ This is the bridge between Servlets and DB.

5. success.jsp
- Shown after registration.
- Displays "Student Registered Successfully!"
- Provides links back to register.html or to view (mapped to ViewStudentsServlet).

6. ViewStudentsServlet.java
- Handles GET requests at /view.
- Calls StudentDAO.getAllStudents().
- Stores the list in request attribute: req.setAttribute("studentList", lst).
- Forwards request to viewStudents.jsp.
ðŸ‘‰ This servlet is the controller for viewing students.

7. viewStudents.jsp
- Retrieves studentList from request.
- Iterates over it using JSP scriptlets.
- Displays all students in a table (ID, Name, Email, Mobile).
- Provides link back to registration.

8. hibernate.cfg.xml
- Defines DB connection (MySQL dac schema).
- Username/password.
- Dialect (MySQLDialect).
- Auto-update schema (hbm2ddl.auto=update).
- Maps com.cdac.Student.
ðŸ‘‰ This is the configuration file for Hibernate ORM.

9. web.xml
- Defines servlet mappings:
- /register â†’ RegisterServlet
- /view â†’ ViewStudentsServlet
- Sets welcome files (so register.html loads first).
ðŸ‘‰ This is the deployment descriptor.

