ðŸš€ Sequence to Write Code (Best Practice Order)
- Model (Student.java) â†’ Define entity first.
- DAO (StudentDAO.java) â†’ Write DB logic.
- Config (hibernate.cfg.xml) â†’ Setup DB connection.
- Servlets (RegisterServlet, ViewStudentsServlet) â†’ Controllers.
- JSP/HTML (register.html, success.jsp, viewStudents.jsp) â†’ Views.
- web.xml â†’ Wire everything together.

âœ… How It All Connects
- HTML/JSP â†’ User interface.
- Servlets â†’ Controllers handling requests.
- DAO + Hibernate â†’ Database persistence.
- Entity (Student) â†’ Maps DB table.
- web.xml â†’ Glue that maps URLs to servlets.

Rushikesh, since youâ€™re building a Library Management System, this flow is a mini MVC pattern. Registration and viewing students are two modules. You can extend this same structure for Books, Issuing, Returning by creating new entities, DAOs, and servlets.
